<div id="review_56737380" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/56737380" />
    <a title="Tiffany" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/195356-tiffany"><img alt="Tiffany" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1216758648p2/195356.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/56737380?book_show_action=true">May 20, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tiffany" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tiffany" href="/user/show/195356-tiffany">Tiffany</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780385720373" href="/book/show/108621.In_the_Eye_of_the_Sun">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer56737380" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8275156314540040036">This book was recently recommended to me by an Egyptian feminist who said, &quot;Read this book, and you&apos;ll understand everything we go through.&quot; While I didn&apos;t find this book to be as analytical as &quot;A Border Passage&quot; - it is billed as fiction, after all - I thought &quot;In the Eye of the Sun&quot; was deeply reflective and moving. As a woman living in Egypt, educated in the West (as a grad student, no less), and struggling to understand the WHY of things here, I thought it was an excellent read. I don&apos;t know</span>
  <span id="freeText8275156314540040036" style="display:none">This book was recently recommended to me by an Egyptian feminist who said, "Read this book, and you'll understand everything we go through." While I didn't find this book to be as analytical as "A Border Passage" - it is billed as fiction, after all - I thought "In the Eye of the Sun" was deeply reflective and moving. As a woman living in Egypt, educated in the West (as a grad student, no less), and struggling to understand the WHY of things here, I thought it was an excellent read. I don't know that I've ever read such an evocative portrayal of a submissive female (although the word itself is never used). I read this very long book in about 4 days and could hardly put it down.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8275156314540040036" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


